            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>1519 Green St.	Oct. 10. 1877.<lb/>
            Rev. S. Morais.<lb/></p>
            <p>546. N. Fifth St.<lb/>
            My Rev. &#38; Dear Sir.<lb/></p>
            <p>To you I went first for encouragement to<lb/> ask an interview&#44; and now I respectfully invite you&#44; to meet two or three<lb/> other Israelites at my residence&#44; 1519 Green St. on Tuesday next at 7 1<lb/>2<lb/> O&#39;clock P. M. Oct. 16&#8212;devoutly to seek out and if possible to discover that<lb/> to put away the stumbling stones on which some of our most<lb/> learned and confident fall and are broken&#44; shaking the faith of<lb/> a multitude in the scripture canon&#44; and putting contempt on the hope<lb/> of the promise made of God unto our fathers&#44; Abraham and Isaac and<lb/> Jacob.  I know you have little hope of any good to come of the meet&#45;<lb/>ing&#44; as you frankly said&#44; when you promised if possible to attend&#58; but<lb/> when we consider Jacob&#39;s dispersion&#44; and the church&#39;s division&#44; all over<lb/> the world&#44; is a calamity and a shame to both alike&#44; full of disappoin&#45;<lb/>ted hope&#44; if we shall find that the cause&#44; as well as confusion&#44;<lb/> is common to us&#44; both Jews &#38; Gentiles&#44; we will help together against the<lb/> common enemy&#44; and banish him from the synagogue and from the<lb/> micveh&#91;&#63;&#93;.  And in whom can any man trust who denies the truth of<lb/> God&#39;s word&#63;  The earth &#38; the heavens shall perish&#59; but his promise given<lb/> shall never fail nor be forgotten&#44; until it is paid to last farthing.<lb/></p>
            <p>In this faith strengthen one another for the glory of God.<lb/></p>
            <p>Yours truly<lb/>
            Henry Dana Ward&#91;&#63;&#93;.<lb/></p>
            
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>Rev. S. Morais<lb/>
                546. N. Fifth St.<lb/>
                City.<lb/></p>
        </body>
    </text>
